Uses of Package
fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.vocabularies

Packages that use fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.vocabularies
fr.loria.synalp.emotionml The main package of LORIA/SYNALP EmotionML. 
fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.descriptors Contains all the aspects that describe an Emotion including Category, Dimension, Appraisal and ActionTendency. 
fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.processors Contains all processors, exporters/importers and validators for EmotionML. 
fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.vocabularies Contains elements related to Vocabularies. 
fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.vocabularies.predefined Contains all predefined vocabularies that can be found on http://www.w3.org/TR/emotion-voc/xml. 
 

Classes in fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.vocabularies used by fr.loria.synalp.emotionml
Vocabulary
          A Vocabulary describes a list of possible values for a descriptor type.
VocabularyReferrer
          A VocabularyReferrer is an InfoCarrier that carries information about vocabulary URIs, that is category set, dimension set, appraisal set and action tendency set.
VocabularyType
          A VocabularyType is the type of Vocabulary which is either CATEGORY, DIMENSION, APPRAISAL and ACTION_TENDENCY.
